entries.femaleVariant: OK, so, lemme hear what this's all about.
entries.maleVariant: OK, so lemme hear what this's all about.

entries.femaleVariant: Nah, no, no, no, no... Loops, cycles. One chapter ends, another begins. Life's full of 'em. Least my guru tells me so.
Mm-hmmm... Hm-hmm... Hm-hmm, hm, uh-huh, uh-huhh, hm-mm...
What's this all about?
Don't recognize that riff.
[pl_pl][Kerry gra na gitarze lub wybija rytm na jakimś meblu (budżet :) ) próbuje różnych melodii, popijając piwo]
Like I said, life's loops.
Um, breakfast cereal?
I'll bite. Tell me about the loops.
Your... guru?
I'll bite – tell me about these "loops."
[pl_pl][zagrywa na gitarze ostrzejszą melodię i nie odpowiada od razu, drocząc się w ten sposób z V, z uśmiechem]
'Cause y'know...  managed well without him. Built my career, made my fortune – me.
But dammit, no matter how hard I try, I can't forget him... Yeah, I'd rip him outta my head if I fuckin' could.
Heh, think I know the feelin'.
entries.maleVariant: Huh, think I know the feelin'.

entries.femaleVariant: Visit Khian every couple o' years. Y'know, he's got this… yurt. In Tangalan. Middle of fuckin' nowhere. Off-grid, net blockers included...
Our last meet... Khian told me that the time for closure, loop completion, had come. That's why we're here – you and me.
Your guru?
Yeah. I got spiritual needs.
And you needed company for that?
What was that little number?
What was that little number? I know it?
entries.maleVariant: What was that little number? I know it.

entries.femaleVariant: And you needed company for that?
entries.maleVariant: Ehh, and you need company for that?
Been thinkin' about that Us Cracks fiasco lately... 'Bout how you helped me. A lot.

entries.femaleVariant: You shake things up, V. 'Fore you came along... I was stuck in the mud – scared to look at my own shadow, even.
entries.maleVariant: You shake things up, V, make me feel… I mean, 'fore you came along I was stuck in mud – scared o' my own shadow, even.

entries.femaleVariant: And now?
Got me thinkin' about a new song – a new album, even! A real fuckin' thrasher with a new soul. Like everything from now on...
Had what I think folks call – an epiphany.
Epiphany? Sounds more like maturity.
We'll see how that works out for you.
"Bleed the Beat." Eh, wrote it during a cruise ship gig. Decks, pools, more pools, buffets – y'know, shrimp. Y'know, bells 'n' whistles.
Eh, could just be what folks call "maturity."
entries.maleVariant: Could just be what folks call "maturity."

entries.femaleVariant: Well, we'll see how that works out for you.
entries.maleVariant: Well, heh, we'll see how that works out for you.

entries.femaleVariant: You'll see. No more mayhem, no more shady-ass schemes. Done with that.
Well... startin' tomorrow.
Nice axe.
Wanna bet? I'm done with all the mayhem, shady-ass schemes. Startin' a new chapter – startin' a new me.
Happy for ya, Ker.
But... y'know, startin' tomorrow.
And see this rusty color on the strings? S'posed to be the blood of legendary bluesman Dennis Ford himself.
It's a Lancaster, custom-built. Only five ever made in this series. I got one. Militech chief's got another. The other three – yeah, fuck if I know.
It's tailored with a reversed-polarity pickup, ebony frets, and one silky-smooth Kaimar vibrato.
That your song? Don't recognize it.
OK. So, first tune I ever wrote that was worth a damn, I wrote at sea.
'Cause it's new. Riff's been bouncin' 'round my skull for a while, now...
I... feel I'm onto somethin' really special here.
So what's with these loops?
This got anything to do with the past? With Johnny?
And d'ya notice? Fingers're onto somethin' fresh again today. There's a loop for ya.
This closure... got anything to do with Johnny? With you battling shadows?
entries.maleVariant: This, um, closure... s'got anything to do with Johnny? With you battling shadows?

entries.femaleVariant: Ehh... nah. Um, well... Yeah maybe a bit? Huh…
Huh.
Everybody thinks the song's about stickin' it to corpo fascistas.
But actually it's...?
Didn't just make music on that boat. Busted my ass servin' drinks, waitin' tables. Free time, I-I composed till my fingers bled.
Had to watch out not to stain their precious porcelain. And there it is – a song about bleedin' in service of the rich. People hear what they wanna hear, though.
But man, was that a hit... One of Samurai's biggest. Just like this one'll be. Fresh, raw, real.
Hm-mm, hmm-mm... Hm hm hm... Ah, hm-hm-hm, ah, hm-hmmm...  Ah, hm-hm-hm-hmmm-mm-mm...
Nice guitar.
Well, don't say it like that...

entries.maleVariant: Not just your company. I needed you, V.

entries.femaleVariant: Been thinkin' 'bout that Us Cracks fiasco lately... 'Bout how you helped me. A lot.
